{
  "stem": "3382.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So before the war, in those years, my family consisted of [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] three children-- I, my sister Esther, my brother-- I think probably either [?",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Zachary ?] or [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH], and, of course, my father and my mother.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But then my father was drafted into the Russian army when the war-- in 1914, the World War I.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] I remember quite, you know, a lot some, I would say, fantasies of my mother.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She had a painted portrait of herself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Odessa, I didn't go to public schools because-- I don't know why.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Because when my father was drafted in the army-- so around 1915, when I was about four and a half or five years old-- I was four and a half.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was winter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "She liquidated the business-- I don't know on whose advice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we moved out from Odessa.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We moved out first to a city called Yelisavetgrad.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] It seems to me, in Russian-- in Soviet times, it used to be called Zinovyevsk.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "That's not important.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And from there, we'll moved to Kherson.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It is a larger city on the river Dnieper, a well-known port which used to export a, a, a lot of grain.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was very-- Dnieper, in that place, was a very large river, like Hudson, whose-- sea ships coming up to pick up wares, or whatever they had.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And in Kherson, I know they-- my mother-- or whoever was there behind it-- bought a small hotel.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I remember it was called [NON-ENGLISH], 'France.' And it was on the [NON-ENGLISH] Street, near the intersection with the Torgovaya Street.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Torgovaya means the 'commerce' street-- [NON-ENGLISH SPEECH], more or less.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
